Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Salvatore, Concetta, Fortunato, Nunzie, Rocco, Rudolfo, Sal, Saverio.","Italian: from a short form of a personal name ending with<i>-gitto</i>, such as <i>Ambrogitto</i>, a pet form of<i>Ambrogio</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Angharad","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Old Celtic intensive prefix <i>an-</i> + <i>cār</i> ‘love’ + the noun suffix <i>-ad</i>. This was the name of the mother of the 12th-century chronicler  Giraldus Cambrensis  (‘Gerald the Welshman’). In the <i>Mabinogi</i>, Angharad Golden Hand at first rejects Peredur's suit, but later falls in love with him when he comes back as the unknown Mute Knight. The name has been strongly revived in Wales since the 1940s, borne, for example, by the actress  Angharad Rees  (  1949-2012 )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Angharad ap Gitto was born about 1454, in Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom, her father, Gitto ap David, was 36 and her mother, ap Thomas, was 30. She had at least 3 sons and 1 daughter with Jevan Ap Gwilim."},"et":{"abt. 1454–":"umbes 1454–Surnud","1452–Female":"1452–Surnud","1454–Female":"1454–Surnud","1462–Male":"1462–Surnud","1480–Male":"1480–Surnud","1480–Female":"1480–Surnud","1490–Male":"1490–Surnud","1644–Male":"1644–Surnud","1420–Male":"1420–Surnud","1426–Female":"1426–Surnud","about 1480":"umbes 1480","abt 1490":"umbes 1490","1462":"1462","abt. 1454":"umbes 1454","1480":"1480","abt. 1480":"umbes 1480","1490":"1490","1426":"1426","1644":"1644","1454":"1454","about 1644":"umbes 1644","1420":"1420","1452":"1452","Wales":"Wales","of Glyn-Nedd, Glmrgn., Wls.":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales","of Altgwawrddu, Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"abt. 1454–":"noin 1454–Kuollut","1452–Female":"1452–Kuollut","1454–Female":"1454–Kuollut"